In this article, President Barack Obama delivers a video message to the AGOA Forum in Nairobi, Kenya. He reflects on his recent trip to Ghana and emphasizes the importance of Africa's potential and its connection to the global economy. Obama highlights the significance of the African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA) in promoting trade and economic growth between Africa and the United States. He acknowledges that while AGOA has been successful in transforming the U.S.-African trade relationship, there is still untapped potential. Obama emphasizes the need for good governance, strong institutions, and investment-friendly environments to achieve lasting prosperity in Africa. He pledges the support and partnership of the United States in developing these aspects and promoting clean energy and agricultural development in Africa. Obama concludes by expressing confidence in Africans' ability to achieve their dreams and thanking the participants of the AGOA Forum.